What do you plan on doing once you've developed the game?The aim is to try and get the game Greenlit on steam. This means we'll have an amazing platform to get the game out, so as many people as possible can enjoy it. If we reach our goal and with enough demand, we'll possibly add a multiplayer aspect to the game in the future.On a final note,You shape this game.

Risks and Challenges
As with any other game in development, there is no guarantee that we will be able to produce the game on time, due to setbacks such as personal issues.
Rest assured though, if this were to ever happen (which we're sure it wont), we will endeavour to get the game to you, as soon as possible.
No matter what we run into, we want you with us every step of the way.
